@startuml SSH Bastion HA Workflow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBorderColor #333333
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
  LifeLineBorderColor #999999
  ArrowColor #333333
  GroupBorderColor #AAAAAA
}

title SSH Bastion HA — Authentication & Access Workflow

actor "User\n(m.bulushev / admin1 / dba1)" as User
box "lb-node\n192.168.56.10" #F0F8FF
  participant "HAProxy\n:22" as HAProxy
end box
box "bastion-01 / bastion-02\n192.168.56.11 / .12" #F0FFF0
  participant "SSHD" as SSHD
  participant "PAM\n(pam-keycloak-oidc)" as PAM
  participant "SSSD" as SSSD
  participant "autofs" as Autofs
end box
box "idp-node\n192.168.56.20" #FFF8F0
  participant "Keycloak\n:8080" as KC
  participant "OpenLDAP\n:389" as LDAP
end box
box "storage-node\n192.168.56.50" #FFF0F5
  participant "NFS Server" as NFS
end box
box "test-server\n192.168.56.60" #F5F0FF
  participant "PostgreSQL 16\n:5432" as PG
end box

== SSH Authentication ==

User -> HAProxy : SSH connect :22
note right of HAProxy
  Firewall: public zone
  allows only SSH
end note

HAProxy -> SSHD : round-robin forward\n(bastion-01 or bastion-02)
note right of SSHD
  Firewall: accepts SSH
  only from 192.168.56.10
end note

SSHD -> PAM : keyboard-interactive\n(prompt for password)
PAM -> User : password prompt
User -> PAM : enters password

PAM -> KC : POST /realms/bastion-realm\n/protocol/openid-connect/token\n(direct access grant)
note right of KC
  Firewall: internal-bastion zone
  ports 8080, 389
  from 192.168.56.0/24
end note

KC -> KC : validate credentials\n& check role:\nbastion-pam-authentication

alt credentials valid + role present
  KC --> PAM : access token\n(with pam_roles claim)
  PAM --> SSHD : auth SUCCESS
else invalid credentials or missing role
  KC --> PAM : 401 Unauthorized
  PAM --> SSHD : auth FAILURE
  SSHD --> User : Permission denied
end

== Session Setup ==

SSHD -> SSSD : resolve user (NSS)
SSSD -> LDAP : ldapsearch\ndc=bastion,dc=local
LDAP --> SSSD : uid, gid, shell, home
SSSD --> SSHD : user info

SSHD -> Autofs : access /home/<username>
Autofs -> NFS : mount\n192.168.56.50:/export/home/<user>
NFS --> Autofs : NFS share
Autofs --> SSHD : home directory ready

SSHD --> User : shell session on bastion

== Outbound Access (from bastion) ==

User -> PG : psql (dba1 only)\nvia 192.168.56.60:5432
note right of PG
  Firewall: accepts SSH & :5432
  only from .11 and .12
  rejects all other SSH
end note
PG --> User : database session

== Host Access ==

actor "Host machine" as Host
Host -> KC : http://localhost:8080\n(Vagrant port forward)
note right of KC
  public zone also
  opens port 8080
  for NAT interface
end note
KC --> Host : Keycloak Admin Console

@enduml
